Single Cell Report

Here we have a example of the single cell analisis of 6 samples from prostate from mouse. I would do the cell ranger execution in a process in nextflow in order to execute in HPC and the upload the h5 data to analice nad visualice in R, calling a Rmarkdown also with nextflow.

I made this analisys at my actual work as a single cell analisys service which we provide to another reserch center. I remove some details about the samples and conclusion in order to not share any sensible data. This analisys was not designed for trayectory analisys but I add some at the end.

Violin plot of raw data. For every sample we can see the distribution of the values of the variables nFeatures(number of genes by cell), nCount( number of count by cell) and percent.mt which is the mitocondrial RNA percetange found by cell

After filtering by number of genes by cell(nFeatures) higher than 100 and by mitocondrial percentage lower than 25

Find cluster and markers.

In this graph(UMAP) every point is a cell and each colour is a different samples. The position in the graph its depend on the expression of the cell, then all the similar cell should cluster together. Here we can see the 3 samples integration its very good, the population of the samples are similar, which is a good indicator of the quality.

In this UMAP we calculate and represent the clustering of the cells. Each group should represent a different cellular type or subtype. We found 11 cluster at this level of resolution(0.1).

Its the same representation than before but split by sample, here we can see in the sample NSD2 there are more cells of the cluster 0 and less of the cluster 1. But all of the are consistent.

Now we represent the features, counts and mitochondrial.percent by cluster. We can see the cluster 10(red circle) has very few genes by cells, it must be a technical noise. All other cluster looks good enough.

Mouse SC

In this heatmap we can see the top 5 genes differentially expressed by cluster. In the next slides we can see the expression of this genes in the UMAP representation.

Cluster1

October 2022 Using the same markers on this paper and the web app CellMarker we can identify our clusters. Also we save the most expresed genes in a csv.
